    <stitle>AFC 95901 - Install Refrigerant Compressor Support</stitle>
    <afc id="AFC95901">
        <afcnum>95901</afcnum>
        <afcdate>February, 1995</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subject>Install Refrigerant Compressor Support</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Cummins</vendor>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This AFC applies to all models with N14 Cummins engines and air conditioning built between
                    09/09/1993 and 10/13/1994 at the Chatham assembly plant, and 09/14/1993 and 11/14/1994 at the
                    Springfield assembly plant.
                </para>
                <para>It is possible that over a period to time, the engine front cover may crack on the abovementioned
                    vehicles because there is not enough support between the refrigerant compressor mounting bracket and
                    the engine. To improve the mounting of the refrigerant compressor, a support has been added between
                    the refrigerant compressor mounting bracket and the engine, along with replacing the outboard
                    compressor mounting bolt with a longer bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590101">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9590101" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9590101" filename="../afcfigures/g9590101.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
