        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the eight (8) bolts that secure the refrigerant compressor to the mounting
                    bracket and remove the belt from the compressor clutch.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put a pry bar in the adjusting slot in the compressor mounting bracket and raise the
                    compressor to the top of the adjusting slots. Tighten one of the mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the outboard mounting bracket bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590101">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and replace it with a 1/2 inch x 1-1/2 inch bolt and
                    1/2 inch flat washer.
                    <emph type="bold">Be sure to install the washer with the bolt.</emph>
                    Tighten to 70-85 ft-lbs. (95-115 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt that secures the strap to the compressor mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590101">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Discard the bolt. Save the nut and washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten the support to the inside of the compressor mounting bracket as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590101">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    with a 3/8 inch x 1-1/2 inch bolt; re-use the nut and washers removed in Step 4.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten the other end of the support to the engine as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590101">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    with a 3/8 inch bolt x 1 inch bolt and 3/8 inch flat washer. Tighten both 3/8 inch bolts to 30-38
                    ft-lbs. (41-51 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the belt on the compressor clutch pulley, tension to 100 lbs. Tighten the
                    compressor mounting bolts to 19-23 ft-lbs. (25-31 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
